## Probe Classification Fix

Problem found:

scripts/probe-native-poller.mjs restored the bridge in the finally block even when called with --keep-bridge-running. It also could classify a bridge-assisted completion as native_pass because native_pass only checked completed trigger plus ACK rows.

Change:

- Introduced stopForProbe = !has("--keep-bridge-running").
- Added bridge_mode to the JSON result.
- Only restore the LaunchAgent when the probe actually stopped it.
- Added bridge_assisted_pass.
- native_pass is now true only when stopForProbe is true and the trigger completes with an ACK.
- A bridge-running completion now reports bridge_assisted_poller_passed_native_unproven instead of native_poller_passed.

Classification test:

node scripts/probe-native-poller.mjs --keep-bridge-running --watch-seconds 25 --hash T5K_KEEP_RUNNING_CLASSIFICATION_20260523T1342Z

Result:

exit=2
bridge_mode=kept_running_bridge_assisted_probe
message=06ec20a8-81a0-456b-beb0-2781b6324504
trigger=abb346e3-7d1a-4eec-8675-7b74962d9c48
bridge_assisted_pass=false
native_pass=false
verdict=native_poller_still_blocked

The important evidence is that --keep-bridge-running no longer performs a bridge stop/restore, and cannot produce native_pass unless the bridge was intentionally stopped for a native-only probe.

## Bridge Queue Hardening

Problem found:

The bridge was spending agent turns on response messages such as plain "ACK trigger ..." and "Posted the Pentagon response ...". Those are terminal status responses, not new work instructions. Treating them as normal work can create noisy reply loops and delay fresh repo-specific tasks.

Change:

scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs now classifies terminal messages when the first token is:

- *_ACK
- *_BLOCKED
- ACK
- BLOCKED

It also classifies first lines starting with "Posted the Pentagon response" as terminal.

Dry-run evidence after restart:

Command:

node scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs --dry-run --limit 12 --max-age-seconds 900

Result:

The first twelve inspected pending triggers included stale ACK/status responses and were classified as would_complete_terminal, including:

- 2e62ab65-f2f9-4046-ad5c-6e1cd0df0fe2 content_preview="MAYA_NATIVE_POLLER_ACK T5I_NATIVE_POLLER_PROBE_20260523T132044Z"
- ede4fcf6-4d96-4e67-b62b-845359056e65 content_preview="ACK trigger d65b0240..."
- fc5c4149-29b8-40ca-a821-5e04b5dc8572 content_preview="Posted the Pentagon response for trigger 931a7cb9..."
- 9c28a7f4-5176-4258-8996-102872a6923a content_preview="ACK trigger 7df6855a-b8fb-4ba8-b453-c0ee2a5ccc3e..."

LaunchAgent was restarted with:

launchctl kickstart -k gui/$(id -u)/run.pentagon.trigger-bridge

